article.description: Jonah Hodges ran for 176 yards and four touchdown in 11 attempts to lead San Diego to a 52-3 pasting of Davidson on Saturday.
article.headline: Hodges, San Diego erupt on offense in 42-3 win over Davidson
article.linkText: Hodges, San Diego erupt on offense in 42-3 win over Davidson
article.story: SAN DIEGO -- Jonah Hodges ran for 176 yards and four touchdowns in 11 attempts to lead San Diego to a 52-3 pasting of Davidson on Saturday. Hodges scored four straight touchdowns on runs of 2, 6, 68 and 2 yards respectively lifting the Toreros to a 35-0 lead with 7:58 remaining before halftime. Hodges tied a school record for rushing touchdowns, matching JT Rogan, Jon Polk and Oscar Arzu. Jereke Armstrong started the scoring with a 2-yard touchdown run three minutes into the contest. Anthony Lawrence completed a 7-yard touchdown pass to Ross Dwelley to make it 42-0 at the break. The Toreros amassed 640 offensive yards to 230 for Davidson. San Diego (4-1, 3-0 Pioneer Football League) has now won 25 consecutive conference games at home. Taylor Mitchell was 8 for 20 passing for and 143 yards for Davidson (2-4, 0-3).
